.TH SDL_SetWindowModal 3 "SDL 3.1.3" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_SetWindowModal \- Toggle the state of the window as modal\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_video\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "bool SDL_SetWindowModal(SDL_Window *window, bool modal);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
To enable modal status on a window, the window must currently be the child
window of a parent, or toggling modal status on will fail\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I window
the window on which to set the modal state\[char46]
.TP
.I modal
true to toggle modal status on, false to toggle it off\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns true on success or false on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

